WEBVTT

1
00:00:27.333 --> 00:00:31.833
Wulf? The neighbors had an alibi.
but there was nothing about the janitor.

2
00:00:31.916 --> 00:00:34.833
He has a key to Camilla's apartment.
Could you check that out?

3
00:00:34.916 --> 00:00:37.625
- Do you think it was him?
- No.

4
00:00:40.208 --> 00:00:41.166
No.

5
00:00:42.833 --> 00:00:43.833
I'll call you.

6
00:00:48.625 --> 00:00:52.291
Is this the one... Camilla was shot with?

7
00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:56.375
Yes. we're pretty sure about that.
We just have to double-check.

8
00:00:56.458 --> 00:01:00.500
It's difficult to know
with close range shots through the skull.

9
00:01:02.416 --> 00:01:03.333
Yeah...

10
00:01:04.458 --> 00:01:06.083
It was the same with Ellen. so...

11
00:01:15.375 --> 00:01:17.750
What makes a guy point a gun

12
00:01:17.833 --> 00:01:21.583
at the head of a defenseless girl
and just pull the trigger?

13
00:01:22.958 --> 00:01:24.500
Fuck if I know.

14
00:01:24.583 --> 00:01:27.208
I guess it's the usual stuff. Hate.

15
00:01:28.166 --> 00:01:31.125
<i>Love. Lunacy.</i>

16
00:01:32.250 --> 00:01:33.416
What do you think?

17
00:01:34.041 --> 00:01:35.125
Silence.

18
00:01:37.916 --> 00:01:40.250
To silence those goddamn voices.

19
00:01:43.041 --> 00:01:44.000
Maybe.

20
00:01:50.666 --> 00:01:54.916
Hey... That diamond
that was found in Camilla's eye...

21
00:01:56.250 --> 00:02:00.541
- What do you think about that?
- I'm thinking that it's... a diamond.

22
00:02:02.500 --> 00:02:04.458
Anyway. it's all there in the report. so...

23
00:02:04.541 --> 00:02:08.541
Yeah. but I'm here to ask if you have
anything that isn't written in the report.

24
00:02:09.291 --> 00:02:10.666
No...

25
00:02:10.750 --> 00:02:12.250
Yeah. or...

26
00:02:12.333 --> 00:02:14.458
Hey. just come have a look at this.

27
00:02:16.083 --> 00:02:18.583
There was something carved into

28
00:02:18.666 --> 00:02:22.000
the beam right above the bed there
that I thought...

29
00:02:23.750 --> 00:02:27.000
Yeah. it's done by a boy.
definitely not a 20-year-old girl.

30
00:02:27.541 --> 00:02:28.541
Okay.

31
00:02:30.916 --> 00:02:35.083
But the diamond. that's for us. at least.

32
00:02:35.833 --> 00:02:36.875
What do you mean?

33
00:02:38.791 --> 00:02:42.375
He left the body in the water to wash away
everything he didn't want us to find.

34
00:02:42.458 --> 00:02:44.000
but he wanted us to find that.

35
00:02:45.666 --> 00:02:49.041
And then we have the finger.
but maybe that's more like...

36
00:02:49.833 --> 00:02:51.458
Well. a trophy.

37
00:02:54.666 --> 00:02:58.375
Are you thinking that this is someone
who might want to continue?

38
00:03:00.166 --> 00:03:01.375
Why would I think that?

39
00:03:01.458 --> 00:03:04.500
Well. you have studied serial murders
in America. so...

40
00:03:04.583 --> 00:03:06.208
And when you see a hammer...

41
00:03:06.291 --> 00:03:08.416
All murders look like nails.

42
00:03:09.708 --> 00:03:10.833
No...

43
00:03:10.916 --> 00:03:12.708
No. I don't think so.

44
00:03:13.750 --> 00:03:16.625
Why not? This is pretty unusual.

45
00:03:17.291 --> 00:03:19.958
Yeah. but serial killers are...

46
00:03:21.250 --> 00:03:23.583
like white whales. They're very rare.

47
00:03:25.291 --> 00:03:28.916
Is there a small part of you hoping
that this is a white whale. perhaps?

48
00:03:32.375 --> 00:03:33.708
There's no white whale.

49
00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:35.333
No?

50
00:03:35.416 --> 00:03:37.500
No. I don't hope so either.

51
00:03:37.583 --> 00:03:40.166
But this guy here
is trying to tell us something.

52
00:04:24.541 --> 00:04:25.875
I don't like this.

53
00:04:26.375 --> 00:04:28.083
<i>No. I know it's not ideal.</i>

54
00:04:28.166 --> 00:04:31.083
<i>but without Olsen.
you need to handle the weapons sales.</i>

55
00:04:31.166 --> 00:04:33.083
We just raided the place.

56
00:04:33.166 --> 00:04:36.500
<i>That is exactly why it will be
the last place they'll look.</i>

57
00:04:36.583 --> 00:04:39.291
<i>If we get the two biggest gangs
in Oslo to start a war.</i>

58
00:04:39.375 --> 00:04:42.875
<i>they'll do our job for us
by taking each other out.</i>

59
00:04:42.958 --> 00:04:44.875
<i>Give Dearpmis and Korps automatic weapons.</i>

60
00:04:44.958 --> 00:04:48.208
<i>and everybody will see
that the police will have to be armed.</i>

61
00:04:48.291 --> 00:04:50.500
Okay. I'll trust you.

62
00:04:54.166 --> 00:04:55.333
Wait here.

63
00:05:01.083 --> 00:05:02.500
Do you have the money?

64
00:05:02.583 --> 00:05:04.791
Not until I've seen
what you've got with you.

65
00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:14.125
Odin?

66
00:05:15.333 --> 00:05:18.750
You smell like a damn cop.

67
00:05:20.625 --> 00:05:23.000
The goods are inside.
Should we have a look?

68
00:05:25.208 --> 00:05:26.208
Looking good?

69
00:05:28.208 --> 00:05:29.250
Now we're talking.

70
00:05:31.166 --> 00:05:35.750
Rumor has it Korps
recently got hold of automatic weapons.

71
00:05:36.625 --> 00:05:39.791
- What do you know about that?
- A lot of fucking questions.

72
00:05:39.875 --> 00:05:42.625
- Yes.
- Do you want the weapons or not?

73
00:05:42.708 --> 00:05:44.041
When is the next delivery?

74
00:05:44.125 --> 00:05:45.250
Next week.

75
00:05:45.333 --> 00:05:46.666
Here.

76
00:05:48.333 --> 00:05:51.666
You couldn't find a place where people
don't fuck through the wall?

77
00:05:51.750 --> 00:05:53.666
No. I couldn't.

78
00:05:53.750 --> 00:05:55.250
This is perfect.

79
00:05:59.708 --> 00:06:02.083
Korps won't get
their weapons until tomorrow.

80
00:06:02.666 --> 00:06:05.541
Now is your chance to get rid
of the competition for good.

81
00:06:13.208 --> 00:06:14.333
<i>Yes. Prince?</i>

82
00:06:14.833 --> 00:06:16.375
The trap is set.

83
00:06:16.458 --> 00:06:17.916
<i>Okay. Good work.</i>

84
00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:21.458
We must find another way.
I can't keep being exposed like this.

85
00:06:21.541 --> 00:06:24.833
Next week's delivery is
eight times larger. It won't work.

86
00:06:24.916 --> 00:06:26.375
We have to find someone else.

87
00:06:26.458 --> 00:06:28.250
<i>Do you have someone in mind?</i>

88
00:06:28.333 --> 00:06:29.791
Yes. I have an idea but...

89
00:06:29.875 --> 00:06:31.791
He needs to be recruited first.

90
00:06:41.416 --> 00:06:43.041
EDITOR-IN-CHIEF

91
00:06:43.708 --> 00:06:45.166
- Hello.
- Hello.

92
00:06:46.291 --> 00:06:48.416
Walk with me.
I'm off to a meeting.

93
00:06:48.500 --> 00:06:49.500
Yes. Okay.

94
00:06:50.291 --> 00:06:52.375
Listen. I have to be honest.

95
00:06:52.458 --> 00:06:55.708
If Haugen and Vik weren't
on summer vacation right now. I...

96
00:06:55.791 --> 00:06:59.125
I wouldn't have given this case to you.
since you're so new.

97
00:07:00.083 --> 00:07:00.916
Okay.

98
00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:03.666
The Camilla Loen murder is
the biggest case we have.

99
00:07:03.750 --> 00:07:04.958
and you wanted crime.

100
00:07:05.041 --> 00:07:05.916
Yes.

101
00:07:06.458 --> 00:07:07.666
So what do you think?

102
00:07:08.375 --> 00:07:11.583
Well... We have all the right ingredients.

103
00:07:11.666 --> 00:07:16.625
It's been five days and the police only
have the murder weapon found in the trash.

104
00:07:16.708 --> 00:07:19.166
No strangers have been seen
around the building.

105
00:07:19.250 --> 00:07:22.250
Only one neighbor heard something
that could've been a shot.

106
00:07:23.666 --> 00:07:25.375
And no signs of forced entry.

107
00:07:25.958 --> 00:07:28.708
The police think she let
the perpetrator inside herself.

108
00:07:28.791 --> 00:07:32.000
but no one
in her social circle is a suspect.

109
00:07:32.083 --> 00:07:33.958
They all have decent alibis.

110
00:07:35.208 --> 00:07:36.083
Okay.

111
00:07:37.250 --> 00:07:39.208
Maya Ek. don't disappoint me.

112
00:07:40.916 --> 00:07:42.541
Keep us posted 24/7.

113
00:07:42.625 --> 00:07:43.916
Yes. definitely.

114
00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:44.958
Good.

115
00:07:46.750 --> 00:07:47.666
See you.

116
00:07:48.875 --> 00:07:50.041
<i>Any suspects?</i>

117
00:07:50.125 --> 00:07:51.041
Nothing.

118
00:07:52.083 --> 00:07:56.208
We've knocked on doors.
talked to the local shop owners.

119
00:07:56.291 --> 00:07:59.666
We've talked to all the cab drivers
that were in the area.

120
00:07:59.750 --> 00:08:03.166
We've checked the alibis
of all the relevant acquaintances.

121
00:08:03.250 --> 00:08:04.875
but nothing stands out.

122
00:08:06.250 --> 00:08:08.958
{\an8}I don't get it.
They're talking about new discoveries.

123
00:08:09.041 --> 00:08:12.416
<i>Aftenposten</i> knows about the finger
and the diamond under her eyelid.

124
00:08:12.500 --> 00:08:14.250
It sounds a lot like a leak.

125
00:08:14.750 --> 00:08:15.791
Maybe a...

126
00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:19.750
drunk who needs some more money for booze?

127
00:08:33.375 --> 00:08:35.250
I seem to remember that we fired you.

128
00:08:37.500 --> 00:08:40.083
I'm getting paid
for the rest of the month.

129
00:08:40.166 --> 00:08:43.041
so I suppose I need
to come to work in the meantime. boss.

130
00:08:48.458 --> 00:08:51.458
If you think that this isn't serious.
Harry. you're wrong.

131
00:08:52.500 --> 00:08:55.208
Your ID card will expire
on the last day of the month.

132
00:08:55.291 --> 00:08:59.208
and you will hand in your service weapon
at the armory office.

133
00:09:02.041 --> 00:09:03.750
I don't understand how you do it.

134
00:09:04.333 --> 00:09:06.708
Drinking yourself
half to death again and again...

135
00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:08.666
And then you just stop?

136
00:09:13.625 --> 00:09:16.500
Okay. if you think you can be useful.
that's fine by me.

137
00:09:16.583 --> 00:09:20.833
You're paid until the end of the month.
But you're not on the Camilla Loen case.

138
00:09:22.375 --> 00:09:24.208
- Why not?
- Waaler is on that case.

139
00:09:24.291 --> 00:09:26.958
You two can't be getting
into a pissing contest.

140
00:10:01.250 --> 00:10:04.833
Missing persons is being handled
by the Crime Unit. We have a murder to...

141
00:10:06.166 --> 00:10:09.666
They'll have to call somebody back
from vacation. I don't have people...

142
00:10:10.416 --> 00:10:14.750
Hold on. Maybe I have...
What did you say the address was?

143
00:10:14.833 --> 00:10:15.916
POLICE

144
00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:18.208
<i>Yes. we do have a man available.</i>

145
00:10:34.791 --> 00:10:36.916
<i>- Yes?</i>
- It's the police.

146
00:10:38.458 --> 00:10:40.208
<i>Top of the building. fifth floor.</i>

147
00:10:40.958 --> 00:10:42.333
Of course it is.

148
00:10:52.250 --> 00:10:56.791
- Hello. Willy Barli.
- Hi. Yes. Detective Hole.

149
00:10:59.833 --> 00:11:00.750
Yes.

150
00:11:01.291 --> 00:11:04.708
So... Lisbeth has gone missing.

151
00:11:05.750 --> 00:11:08.500
So I've been trying
to call her cell phone. but she's

152
00:11:08.583 --> 00:11:10.583
left it at home. and...

153
00:11:11.500 --> 00:11:15.375
I've tried to call the grocery store
and three police stations.

154
00:11:15.458 --> 00:11:19.375
I had to call the National Theater
and see if she'd gone down there.

155
00:11:19.875 --> 00:11:23.958
The premiere is in 11 days.
so she keeps practicing and doesn't sleep.

156
00:11:24.625 --> 00:11:26.708
- Is that her?
- Mm-hmm.

157
00:11:26.791 --> 00:11:27.666
Right.

158
00:11:28.708 --> 00:11:30.000
Soon everybody will know.

159
00:11:30.083 --> 00:11:33.416
so I had to call you
because I need help to--

160
00:11:33.500 --> 00:11:35.958
- Is it just the two of you living here?
- Yes.

161
00:11:38.708 --> 00:11:40.333
Is this where you last saw her?

162
00:11:40.416 --> 00:11:43.625
- Yes. it was right here.
- Hello.

163
00:11:45.666 --> 00:11:46.833
Hey.

164
00:12:02.541 --> 00:12:04.333
When did you last see her?

165
00:12:04.416 --> 00:12:06.375
Two hours and ten minutes ago.

166
00:12:06.458 --> 00:12:09.291
What... your wife's been missing
for two hours?

167
00:12:09.375 --> 00:12:11.958
It's not long.
but she was just going to the store

168
00:12:12.041 --> 00:12:14.375
to buy potato salad for the pork chops.

169
00:12:16.416 --> 00:12:18.541
You've called the hospitals
and the police?

170
00:12:19.041 --> 00:12:22.541
Have you called friends?
Maybe she ran into somebody--

171
00:12:22.625 --> 00:12:25.625
No. Have you heard about someone
walking out in their bikini

172
00:12:25.708 --> 00:12:28.208
to buy potato salad
for freshly grilled pork chops

173
00:12:28.291 --> 00:12:30.333
and takes that opportunity to run away?

174
00:12:35.833 --> 00:12:37.583
I'm going to make some phone calls.

175
00:12:50.500 --> 00:12:51.500
- Hey. hey.
- Hey.

176
00:12:51.583 --> 00:12:54.458
Oh damn. it's hot in here.

177
00:12:54.541 --> 00:12:56.500
Hey. Ivan Bratteng.

178
00:12:56.583 --> 00:13:00.833
- Yes. Harry Hole. hello.
- Where do we start? Where's the husband?

179
00:13:00.916 --> 00:13:03.375
He's in there.
trying to find some of her clothes.

180
00:13:03.458 --> 00:13:06.083
The dog doesn't need
to know her scent necessarily.

181
00:13:06.166 --> 00:13:09.791
This doesn't need to be so serious.
She could be anywhere.

182
00:13:09.875 --> 00:13:12.208
But I want you to search.

183
00:13:12.291 --> 00:13:15.708
Talk to neighbors. look around.
and get another duty officer up here.

184
00:13:15.791 --> 00:13:19.666
I'll stay with him for now. then talk
to the neighbors across the yard.

185
00:13:19.750 --> 00:13:21.916
They can see this apartment from there.

186
00:13:22.791 --> 00:13:24.791
Because you suspect the husband?

187
00:13:25.583 --> 00:13:28.375
Yes. I always suspect
the husband on principle.

188
00:13:29.500 --> 00:13:30.333
Why?

189
00:13:30.416 --> 00:13:33.666
It's always the husband.
Hole's first commandment.

190
00:13:33.750 --> 00:13:36.500
- Could we get started?
- Yup. Yes.

191
00:13:36.583 --> 00:13:38.125
Start with the stairway.

192
00:13:40.166 --> 00:13:41.250
Come on.

193
00:14:15.791 --> 00:14:17.125
Is everything okay. Harry?

194
00:14:17.208 --> 00:14:21.083
- Yes... yes.
- You don't look so well.

195
00:14:21.750 --> 00:14:23.750
Maybe you should take iron supplements.

196
00:14:25.208 --> 00:14:27.291
- Mm-hmm.
- I told...

197
00:14:29.791 --> 00:14:31.375
I always tell Lisbeth that.

198
00:14:34.458 --> 00:14:36.208
Did you notice what just happened?

199
00:14:39.375 --> 00:14:40.958
That I was about to say "told."

200
00:14:45.375 --> 00:14:48.583
- Frank? It's the police.
- What?

201
00:14:48.666 --> 00:14:51.041
- Yeah. Frank.
- Harry Hole.

202
00:14:51.125 --> 00:14:53.541
- Lisbeth's gone missing.
- What are you saying?

203
00:14:53.625 --> 00:14:56.625
Didn't we see them
a couple of hours ago on the balcony?

204
00:14:56.708 --> 00:14:59.791
We hear them all the time.
their balcony door is always open.

205
00:15:01.208 --> 00:15:04.166
Yeah... she was wearing a bikini.
according to the husband.

206
00:15:04.250 --> 00:15:07.083
And high heels. She doesn't leave
the house without them.

207
00:15:08.875 --> 00:15:10.458
What did the neighbors say?

208
00:15:10.541 --> 00:15:13.416
They saw her leave.
He was at home the whole time.

209
00:15:15.708 --> 00:15:20.541
Do you think this might be an exception?

210
00:15:22.208 --> 00:15:23.541
That it's not the husband.

211
00:15:25.541 --> 00:15:27.958
I'm... afraid so.

212
00:15:29.416 --> 00:15:33.500
And if it's not the husband.
do you think there could be a connection?

213
00:15:33.583 --> 00:15:34.583
Why do you think so?

214
00:15:34.666 --> 00:15:36.250
I think that you think that.

215
00:15:38.958 --> 00:15:43.083
If he doesn't alert. that doesn't mean
that your wife hasn't been here.

216
00:15:43.166 --> 00:15:46.666
It's hard for him to distinguish
one smell from everything else.

217
00:15:46.750 --> 00:15:49.291
I don't think there's much else
we can do here now.

218
00:15:52.333 --> 00:15:53.833
It's going to be okay.

219
00:15:53.916 --> 00:15:57.333
No. it's not going to be okay.
I've called everyone we know.

220
00:15:57.916 --> 00:15:59.333
No one's seen her.

221
00:15:59.416 --> 00:16:01.583
All patrol cars have been notified.

222
00:16:01.666 --> 00:16:03.833
We're doing everything to find her.

223
00:16:04.541 --> 00:16:07.041
Was she wearing anything
apart from shoes and a bikini?

224
00:16:07.125 --> 00:16:08.791
She was wearing nail polish.

225
00:16:09.458 --> 00:16:12.416
Just like mine. only it says "Willy" on...

226
00:16:12.500 --> 00:16:14.125
- He's got something!
- ...her...

227
00:16:33.291 --> 00:16:37.833
No. this is not okay.
Oh. it's not okay. this will not be okay.

228
00:16:37.916 --> 00:16:40.958
This is not okay... This is not okay.

229
00:16:48.625 --> 00:16:51.416
[Swedish] <i>Book of Revelation. Chapter 16.</i>

230
00:16:53.708 --> 00:16:57.875
<i>"And the third angel poured out their bowl
into the rivers and springs of water.</i>

231
00:16:57.958 --> 00:16:59.333
<i>and they became blood."</i>

232
00:17:01.541 --> 00:17:06.416
<i>"Come. I will show you the judgment
of the great harlot.</i>

233
00:17:07.000 --> 00:17:08.541
<i>who is lying in the water."</i>

234
00:18:16.083 --> 00:18:17.375
Hey. are you available?

235
00:18:17.458 --> 00:18:19.000
Can't you see I'm reading?

236
00:18:19.083 --> 00:18:20.416
Fucking...

237
00:18:23.166 --> 00:18:25.916
Hey! Are you available?

238
00:18:31.375 --> 00:18:32.833
Where's this guy going?

239
00:18:34.083 --> 00:18:37.083
To... the land of dreams.

240
00:18:37.583 --> 00:18:41.041
Or no. to the land of sleep.
preferably without dreaming.

241
00:18:43.166 --> 00:18:44.500
Are you having nightmares?

242
00:18:48.083 --> 00:18:52.416
I need something that can knock me
out completely. That isn't booze.

243
00:18:52.500 --> 00:18:55.750
- Do you have anything?
- Do I look like a criminal?

244
00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:14.458
What's this?

245
00:19:14.541 --> 00:19:17.708
Let me put it like this.
if you take half of one. you'll sleep.

246
00:19:17.791 --> 00:19:22.416
If you take a whole one...
it'll be night night for a long time.

247
00:19:26.500 --> 00:19:30.500
- I'm short on cash these days...
- Relax. man. Jesus.

248
00:19:31.000 --> 00:19:34.083
That's what friends are for.
Some drugs on a bad day.

249
00:19:42.500 --> 00:19:43.666
Hey...

250
00:19:46.583 --> 00:19:49.166
Do you have anything
that will close the curtains?

251
00:19:58.666 --> 00:20:01.791
- I don't like that look of yours.
- Hey. come on.

252
00:20:05.375 --> 00:20:08.208
- Is it Rakel?
- What makes you think that?

253
00:20:08.291 --> 00:20:11.375
I don't know. I've only known you
since primary school. so...

254
00:20:11.958 --> 00:20:13.083
So why?

255
00:20:22.208 --> 00:20:25.000
You know.
I don't think there's a drug for that.

256
00:20:26.666 --> 00:20:28.958
I can only really think of one thing.

257
00:20:29.041 --> 00:20:30.166
A bullet.

258
00:20:31.208 --> 00:20:33.708
I was going to say... "yourself."

259
00:20:37.083 --> 00:20:38.000
No...

260
00:20:39.333 --> 00:20:40.625
Come on. please.

261
00:21:33.750 --> 00:21:37.458
- You're drunk. Attila will kick you out.
- I don't care.

262
00:21:41.333 --> 00:21:42.333
Who's that?

263
00:21:45.458 --> 00:21:47.208
Dearpmis is so fucked.

264
00:21:47.708 --> 00:21:49.125
Why are you saying that?

265
00:21:49.916 --> 00:21:51.333
Attila has the weapons.

266
00:21:52.750 --> 00:21:54.416
Get your stuff and I'll show you.

267
00:22:00.208 --> 00:22:01.083
Fuck!

268
00:22:05.208 --> 00:22:08.000
Hawk! It's Dearpmis! Run!

269
00:22:08.083 --> 00:22:09.000
Attila!

270
00:22:28.666 --> 00:22:30.333
Come on!

271
00:22:32.166 --> 00:22:33.958
Come on! Go. go. go!

272
00:22:34.041 --> 00:22:35.333
Get the Kalashnikov.

273
00:22:39.041 --> 00:22:40.291
Attila! Here!

274
00:22:47.666 --> 00:22:50.000
Fuck! They have automatic weapons!

275
00:22:50.625 --> 00:22:53.791
Loke! For fuck's sake.
the bastard cop lied to us!

276
00:22:54.625 --> 00:22:55.875
It's a trap!

277
00:22:55.958 --> 00:22:57.250
Pull back!

278
00:23:05.041 --> 00:23:07.666
No! Fuck. Loke!

279
00:23:35.208 --> 00:23:38.000
Hospital now! Go!

280
00:24:26.750 --> 00:24:28.791
- Yes.
<i>- Yes. Prince?</i>

281
00:24:30.666 --> 00:24:32.791
- We have a few casualties.
<i>- I see.</i>

282
00:24:32.875 --> 00:24:34.541
Not as many as we'd hoped.

283
00:24:35.416 --> 00:24:37.333
But they're just getting started so...

284
00:24:37.916 --> 00:24:38.916
<i>Well done.</i>

285
00:25:01.791 --> 00:25:06.708
<i>A young boy is dead after the shootings
between rival gangs Korps and Dearpmis.</i>

286
00:25:06.791 --> 00:25:10.000
<i>The tension between the two gangs
has escalated.</i>

287
00:25:10.083 --> 00:25:11.875
<i>In other news.</i>

288
00:25:11.958 --> 00:25:17.291
<i>the search for Lisbeth Barli continues.
Comment from her sister Toya.</i>

289
00:25:17.375 --> 00:25:19.958
LISBETH BARLI MISSING

290
00:25:20.041 --> 00:25:22.750
How many views does VG have
on Lisbeth Barli's sister?

291
00:25:22.833 --> 00:25:25.125
Uh... 400.000.

292
00:25:26.583 --> 00:25:28.958
I want you
on the Lisbeth Barli story instead.

293
00:25:29.041 --> 00:25:30.958
Barli? But she's just missing.

294
00:25:31.041 --> 00:25:33.000
Did you hear those numbers?

295
00:25:33.083 --> 00:25:36.416
Those sisters have gone
from B to A-list celebrities overnight.

296
00:25:37.041 --> 00:25:40.125
And get a comment from the sister!
I want those numbers.

297
00:25:46.041 --> 00:25:47.208
Maya Ek. <i>Aftenposten</i>.

298
00:25:47.291 --> 00:25:50.208
<i>Hi. Ek. I have a tip.</i>

299
00:25:50.291 --> 00:25:52.125
Okay. About what?

300
00:25:52.208 --> 00:25:54.041
<i>The shooting at the biker club.</i>

301
00:25:54.125 --> 00:25:56.666
<i>Flamethrowers and automatic guns were used.</i>

302
00:25:56.750 --> 00:26:01.333
<i>What will the Minister of Justice do
in terms of arming the police?</i>

303
00:26:01.416 --> 00:26:03.125
<i>How is the city to be defended?</i>

304
00:26:03.208 --> 00:26:04.333
Interesting.

305
00:26:04.916 --> 00:26:07.541
Who am I talking to.
and how do you know this?

306
00:26:08.750 --> 00:26:10.166
[Norwegian] From the inside. Ek.

307
00:26:11.208 --> 00:26:12.666
That's all you need to know.

308
00:26:38.500 --> 00:26:44.291
MISSING
CONTACT THE POLICE

309
00:26:47.208 --> 00:26:49.250
<i>Hi. Harry. This is Willy Barli calling.</i>

310
00:26:49.333 --> 00:26:52.875
<i>I'd like you to put more people
on the search.</i>

311
00:26:52.958 --> 00:26:54.958
<i>because I've heard that if you--</i>

312
00:26:56.166 --> 00:27:02.041
<i>It's Willy Barli again. Maybe we should
set up some sort of monetary reward--</i>

313
00:27:03.250 --> 00:27:05.000
<i>It's me. Willy Barli again.</i>

314
00:27:05.583 --> 00:27:09.833
<i>I've spoken to a clairvoyant woman
the Danish police have used.</i>

315
00:27:09.916 --> 00:27:11.708
<i>and she's seeing Lisbeth in water.</i>

316
00:27:11.791 --> 00:27:14.250
<i>Please call me back.</i>

317
00:27:28.750 --> 00:27:29.833
ANSWERING MACHINE

318
00:27:34.791 --> 00:27:36.625
So annoying when they don't speak.

319
00:27:40.916 --> 00:27:42.375
Heard you were quitting.

320
00:27:44.833 --> 00:27:45.708
Yeah.

321
00:27:47.041 --> 00:27:51.333
What are you going to do instead?
Same old. same old?

322
00:27:51.833 --> 00:27:54.958
Debt collector? Insurance company?

323
00:27:55.041 --> 00:27:56.708
Maybe a security firm?

324
00:27:56.791 --> 00:27:59.083
Always someone who wants
a famous investigator

325
00:27:59.166 --> 00:28:00.916
with a legal background.

326
00:28:03.458 --> 00:28:07.041
They don't know that you killed
a colleague driving under the influence.

327
00:28:08.083 --> 00:28:09.583
Not yet anyway.

328
00:28:14.958 --> 00:28:16.833
We don't like each other. you and I.

329
00:28:17.541 --> 00:28:18.625
Do we?

330
00:28:22.041 --> 00:28:23.041
But...

331
00:28:25.291 --> 00:28:26.291
I respect you.

332
00:28:28.375 --> 00:28:31.708
We're not that different.
Both intelligent.

333
00:28:32.291 --> 00:28:34.666
We don't give a shit
what other people think.

334
00:28:34.750 --> 00:28:37.458
But... you haven't figured out
how to make money.

335
00:28:37.541 --> 00:28:39.791
- What do you want?
- I want to help you.

336
00:28:40.500 --> 00:28:42.541
We don't have to be enemies. you and I.

337
00:28:43.291 --> 00:28:45.791
Sjølid doesn't have
to sign your dismissal.

338
00:28:46.958 --> 00:28:48.000
You understand?

339
00:28:51.791 --> 00:28:55.875
But I have a little project
that I need help with.

340
00:28:59.958 --> 00:29:01.083
Think about it.

341
00:29:44.083 --> 00:29:47.000
<i>Head of Criminal Police Sjølid.
What's the situation?</i>

342
00:29:47.083 --> 00:29:48.541
M207 here.

343
00:29:48.625 --> 00:29:51.791
Patrol car Bravo 42 has crashed
at Majorstua station.

344
00:29:51.875 --> 00:29:54.000
The driver is relatively unharmed. but...

345
00:29:54.541 --> 00:29:56.625
the man in the passenger seat is dead.

346
00:29:58.083 --> 00:30:00.250
Yeah. I think so. he smells like alcohol.

347
00:30:00.333 --> 00:30:04.500
An ambulance is on its way.
I'll stay until the ambulance gets here.

348
00:30:04.583 --> 00:30:06.416
No. there's no one else in the area.

349
00:30:14.958 --> 00:30:16.125
I understand.

350
00:30:16.791 --> 00:30:17.916
Copy.

351
00:30:19.333 --> 00:30:22.833
We're going to... move the dead person
to the driver's seat.

352
00:30:23.333 --> 00:30:24.958
Yes. It's an order.

353
00:30:25.041 --> 00:30:27.833
Not to save the drunk.
but to avoid a scandal.

354
00:30:27.916 --> 00:30:29.458
Go over to the other side.

355
00:30:33.333 --> 00:30:35.583
What are you doing?
This is your fucking fault.

356
00:30:35.666 --> 00:30:38.000
It's your fault. You killed him!

357
00:30:57.541 --> 00:31:03.791
ELLEN GJELTEN

358
00:31:13.625 --> 00:31:15.291
{\an8}ELLEN GJELTEN
REST IN PEACE

359
00:31:15.375 --> 00:31:18.375
{\an8}<i>Thank God we humans
actually get through stuff.</i>

360
00:31:18.458 --> 00:31:21.375
<i>Despite everything. We do survive.</i>

361
00:31:30.916 --> 00:31:33.416
- Talk to me.
<i>- Yes. hi. Ivan Bratteng here.</i>

362
00:31:33.500 --> 00:31:35.208
- Hi.
<i>- We're at Sognsvann now.</i>

363
00:31:35.291 --> 00:31:39.500
We can't find anything here.
How would you like us to proceed?

364
00:31:40.250 --> 00:31:43.416
<i>- Just move along. Keep me posted.</i>
- Yes. Got it.

365
00:31:59.666 --> 00:32:02.833
[Swedish] <i>Open your eyes.</i>

366
00:32:02.916 --> 00:32:04.708
<i>It's a simple pattern.</i>

367
00:32:06.250 --> 00:32:08.541
<i>A red guiding star.</i>

368
00:32:09.458 --> 00:32:11.625
<i>A five-pointed Devil's Cross</i>

369
00:32:12.166 --> 00:32:13.666
<i>will show the way.</i>

370
00:32:31.375 --> 00:32:32.666
How did it go?

371
00:32:35.083 --> 00:32:37.166
Badly. I froze.

372
00:32:38.916 --> 00:32:39.916
Hey...

373
00:32:47.041 --> 00:32:48.250
Why do they drink?

374
00:32:51.166 --> 00:32:52.083
Harry and them.

375
00:32:59.416 --> 00:33:00.833
I don't know. Oleg.

376
00:33:03.000 --> 00:33:05.583
There must be something
that could get him to quit.

377
00:33:06.500 --> 00:33:08.916
Sure. He quits.

378
00:33:09.833 --> 00:33:13.666
- He quits and he starts again.
- But does he really want to be that drunk?

379
00:33:13.750 --> 00:33:16.000
It doesn't look
like he's having a great time.

380
00:33:55.250 --> 00:33:57.458
<i>You have one new message.</i>

381
00:33:57.958 --> 00:33:59.166
<i>Hi. this is Møller.</i>

382
00:33:59.250 --> 00:34:01.958
<i>What are you up to?</i>

383
00:34:02.458 --> 00:34:07.166
<i>I sent you one missing person case.
and you mobilize the entire department.</i>

384
00:34:07.250 --> 00:34:08.625
<i>You can't do that.</i>

385
00:34:09.250 --> 00:34:12.875
<i>I'll send the case
over to the missing persons department.</i>

386
00:34:12.958 --> 00:34:15.416
<i>You don't need to come back to work.</i>

387
00:34:15.916 --> 00:34:17.750
<i>Sorry. but you stay at home.</i>

388
00:34:19.625 --> 00:34:21.791
<i>Remember to return your service weapon.</i>

389
00:34:22.291 --> 00:34:23.583
<i>Goodbye.</i>

390
00:35:02.666 --> 00:35:03.833
Well. well.

391
00:35:06.250 --> 00:35:08.500
The end of yet another career. I see.

392
00:35:09.416 --> 00:35:12.916
For all you know.
I'm just getting a new service weapon.

393
00:35:13.000 --> 00:35:16.083
No. I can tell from looking
into people's eyes who's moving up

394
00:35:16.166 --> 00:35:17.750
and who's stepping down.

395
00:35:22.500 --> 00:35:23.958
How long have you been here?

396
00:35:25.166 --> 00:35:26.250
Far too long.

397
00:35:28.458 --> 00:35:30.333
Was it a good career?

398
00:35:31.458 --> 00:35:33.833
Nah. it's been totally average. Kind of...

399
00:35:34.541 --> 00:35:36.416
Kind of like a roller coaster.

400
00:35:36.500 --> 00:35:38.625
Oh. yeah? Homicide division?

401
00:35:38.708 --> 00:35:40.833
At least you were surrounded
by good people.

402
00:35:42.166 --> 00:35:44.166
Kind of like a roller coaster there too.

403
00:35:48.875 --> 00:35:51.375
Have a nice and aimless life. Harry Hole.

404
00:35:53.458 --> 00:35:55.125
Let's take it...

405
00:35:55.208 --> 00:35:58.208
Let's take it easy. One at a time. please.

406
00:35:58.291 --> 00:35:59.958
Erling Rein. VG.

407
00:36:00.041 --> 00:36:02.875
Camilla Loen has been killed.
Lisbeth Barli is missing.

408
00:36:02.958 --> 00:36:05.125
Do you have no leads in either case?

409
00:36:05.958 --> 00:36:09.708
{\an8}Following up on leads and tips
that don't take us anywhere

410
00:36:09.791 --> 00:36:13.041
{\an8}isn't not getting anywhere.
it's excluding possibilities.

411
00:36:15.750 --> 00:36:17.583
{\an8}POLICE HQ

412
00:36:18.458 --> 00:36:20.625
<i>Lisbeth Barli has been missing
for a while.</i>

413
00:36:20.708 --> 00:36:23.333
<i>What are the chances she's still alive?</i>

414
00:36:23.416 --> 00:36:26.916
We have our best detectives
on the case. working day and night.

415
00:36:27.000 --> 00:36:29.958
Solving these two cases
is our highest priority.

416
00:36:30.041 --> 00:36:31.375
THE POSTAL SERVICE

417
00:36:31.458 --> 00:36:33.791
<i>Next question goes to</i> Aftenposten<i>.</i>

418
00:36:33.875 --> 00:36:37.291
We got a tip that automatic weapons
and flamethrowers were used

419
00:36:37.375 --> 00:36:38.833
during the shooting at Korps.

420
00:36:38.916 --> 00:36:43.500
What is the view of the administration
on the rules regarding arming the police?

421
00:36:45.083 --> 00:36:47.916
The administration
has no comment at this time.

422
00:36:48.000 --> 00:36:49.833
But it must feel unsafe--

423
00:36:49.916 --> 00:36:53.125
This press conference is now over.
Thank you for your attendance.

424
00:36:53.208 --> 00:36:55.125
With so many guns on the streets.

425
00:37:04.583 --> 00:37:10.625
MISSING
CONTACT THE POLICE

426
00:37:30.958 --> 00:37:32.458
<i>Camilla Loen. what do we know?</i>

427
00:37:32.541 --> 00:37:35.750
We know that Camilla Loen
was found in her shower.

428
00:37:35.833 --> 00:37:38.791
and that her finger most likely
was cut off before she died.

429
00:37:39.375 --> 00:37:43.041
- Beate?
- No. No fingerprints. No DNA.

430
00:37:45.083 --> 00:37:46.708
- Wulf?
- We've got nothing.

431
00:37:51.958 --> 00:37:54.416
MURDER INVESTIGATION CHIEF
POLICE HQ. 0190 OSLO

432
00:38:20.708 --> 00:38:21.833
[Swedish] Hi. Dad.

433
00:38:22.458 --> 00:38:24.583
Yes? No. I don't think so.

434
00:38:25.708 --> 00:38:27.291
You shouldn't worry.

435
00:38:47.666 --> 00:38:49.291
- Hey.
- Hey.

436
00:38:49.791 --> 00:38:50.791
One beer.

437
00:38:51.291 --> 00:38:52.416
Hey.

438
00:38:53.041 --> 00:38:54.250
- Hey.
- Hey.

439
00:38:54.333 --> 00:38:55.625
So you're here?

440
00:39:06.958 --> 00:39:08.291
Damn it. Harry.

441
00:39:14.583 --> 00:39:16.541
- Did he answer?
- No.

442
00:39:19.291 --> 00:39:24.000
Let's agree that nobody discusses this
until we know how to proceed.

443
00:41:13.625 --> 00:41:18.583
Subtitle translation by: Trine Friis
